<p style="text-align:left;font-size:16px;line-height:35px;">
TRAVIS CI ACCOUNT CREATION INSTRUCTIONS
</p>

<p style="text-align:left;">
First, thank you for signing up to use Travis CI. We are excited to have you as part of our exclusive beta program.
<br><br>
Travis CI Version Control System (VCS) Proxy allows you to connect Perforce Helix Core and Apache SVN repositories to Travis CI enabling you to benefit from the CI/CD automation that Travis CI offers. 
<br><br>
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:4px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
To start using Travis CI, follow these steps:<br><BR>
1. Verify your email address by going <a href="<%=confirmation_url(@resource, confirmation_token: @token)" target="_blank">here</a>
</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
2. Once your email address is confirmed, please create your own password. To do this, go to <a href="<%= @vcsproxy_link %>" target="_blank">Travis CI VCS Proxy</a> and then select <a href="<%= @vcsproxy_link %>/forgot_password" target="_blank">Forgot Your Password</a>. Then, you will get an email with instructions on how to reset your password.<br>
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:4px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
3. When you log-in with your new password, set up 2 Factor Authentication. This is a necessary security step.<br>
</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4px;text-align:left;color:#333333;">
4. Finally, log in to <a href="<%= @travisci_link %>" target="_blank">Travis CI</a> with the ‘Sign in via Travis CI VCS Proxy’ option and synchronize your account with Travis CI VCS Proxy.
</p>
<br>
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:4px">
After creating your account, start your first build today. Here are a few resources to help you get started quickly and smoothly:<br>
<ul style="text-align:left;">
  <li><a href="https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/for-beginners" target="_blank">Core Concepts of Travis CI</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/travis-ci-vcs-proxy" target="_blank">Understanding the Travis CI VCS Proxy</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/travis-ci-vcs-proxy-get-started/" target="_blank">How to Get Started with Travis CI</a></li>
</ul>
</p>
<br>
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:4px">
Remember, the <a href="https://travis-ci.community" target="_blank">Community Forum</a> is a popular place to ask questions, get answers and obtain ideas.
<br><br>
Any time during the beta, if you want to discuss adopting Travis CI, please contact our Customer Success Team at <a href="mailto:<%= @support_mail %>?Subject=Travis%20CI%20VCS%20Proxy%20-%20Closed%20Beta" style="color:#0068FF;"><%= @support_mail %></a>.  They will work with you to customize a plan specifically for your organization.
<br><br>
If you have trouble creating your account or just need help, feel free to contact  <a href="mailto:<%= @support_mail %>?Subject=Travis%20CI%20VCS%20Proxy%20-%20Closed%20Beta" style="color:#0068FF;"><%= @support_mail %></a>.  This email address has been set up specifically for the beta program and our best support staff is available to answer your questions.
<br><br>
Now you are ready to start using Travis CI.
</p>
